cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on enabling secure connectivity between IoT devices and UAVs. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper mentions end-to-end secure connectivity. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a system model for managing data processing tasks of a heterogeneous wireless sensor network. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses edge computing paradigms for on-site processing and managing capabilities of sensor networks. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves the use of UAVs for managing sensor networks.
